Scabies

A person presents at the pharmacy and asks for something to treat a really itch rash they have on their body. They have been told by a friend it might be scabies.

Details

Questions Case
Who has the problem:
Person presenting or another. Description: Age, sex 		It is for you
What is the problem:
Decription of symptoms. 		It is on my body, it is red and really itchy.
It is especially bad on my wrists and between my fingers.
Treatment for this problem:
Used anything? Is it working? How have used the treatment? How long for? Any other action? 		No, thats why Im here. A friend said it might be scabies.
Medication history:
Prescribed medicines/Non-prescribed/Herbal/vitamins etc.
Anything new or ceased. 		No dont take anything.
Medical history No
Pregnant/breastfeeding No
Past adverse effects with medicine/treatments I dont think so

Image

Expected Outcomes

  • Determine that the patient has scabies
  • Explain that it is an allergic reaction to the mite causes the signs and symptoms of scabies
  • Manage patient expectations as itching can continue for several weeks
  • Offer an antihistamine to manage itch
  • Ensure patient is aware that all members of the household have to be treated
  • Provide adequate instructions on how to use the product
  • Provide extensive non-pharmacological advice
